item.title: Shop Interfaces [rep ++]
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“Wet Dreamss, post:9, topic:421977”][quote author=zyle1992 link=topic=524659.msg3818320#msg3818320 date=1321556986]

Well, i’ve been looking for over an hour now and havn’t managed to find shop interfaces that look like these

[img ]http://i1136.photobucket.com/albums/n490/guner123/ScreenshotStudiocapture208.png[/img ]

My friend liamp’s server has them, and i asked him to toss a brotha a link to them, but his friend has them >.<

So i was just wondering if anybody has shop interfaces like these, if you do For sure Rep ++

Suppose you could ask your friend for the interface data.

I did, he said he didn’t really wanna give me What afriend lolz

Well then make a better interface. There are a lot of details about it that are off (positioning of the close button, gradient mismatch). There are Interface editors that work for this. It also isn’t very hard to do (well, with my interface maker that is).

might i ask what interface maker u use then?

One that I made to fill the gaps the others had. I haven’t released it anywhere. I may in the future, once I clean up the code. I’m actually surprised that the code works with all the hacks in it.

well nice then, wish i was that pro with java XD
Well, i look forward to the release. Any interface editers that you suggest then ^.^

Lin’s in the Client hacking section does a pretty good job. It’s written in C# however, so you may need to install some additional libraries to get it to work (Or just Mono; I can’t remember if he built it with it.)
[/quote]

Alright cool, thanks for the help, Much appreciated (would rep you… but ehhh, you’ve got enuf of that :D)[/quote]

No problem. My server suite has many tools that will make operating a server much easier. One such example is implementing SUIT (my interface library) with XML to produce something like this:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<?xml-stylesheet href="interface.css"?>
<interface id="3233">
    <frame id="inventory">
        <scrollpane>
            <itemtable width="4" length="7" />
        </scrollpane>
    </frame>
</interface>
frame {
    visible: false;
}

#inventory {
    background: url("img/frame/background.jpg");
    visible: true;
}
